The paper deals with the problem of influence maximization on social networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS subfields. The use of social streams and the sliding window model suggests that the paper may belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.SD (Software Engineering). The focus on maintaining a set of k seeds with the largest influence value over the most recent social actions suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the application of influence maximization to viral marketing and network monitoring suggests that the paper may belong to cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
